      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROLL TO THE TOP (9) draws on the back row again but should enjoy a trail and has been producing some good efforts from that line, placing here last week and winning at Young last month. Has winning claims with even luck. SHAUN SHANNON (1) has had some tougher barriers of late but has been producing some decent efforts including a placing from the second row two back at this circuit and distance. The ace draw gives him every chance to show his best. MAJOR JEWEL (2) goes up in grade but has come from wider barriers to finish second in two of her last three outings at this circuit and distance, beaten only 1.4 metres. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw. FLUTTERING ANGEL (4) led and boxed on well for second at Young last start. Has a strong record at this distance so can make an impact.",
